    \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n                                                \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                    \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n                                                        \n                                \n                                                                    \n                                                \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                    \n                                \n    \n    \n        \n                    \n                        \n                                    \n\n\n\n\u003cdiv id=\"article-body\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWindows 11 File Explorer offers many features that allow you to manage data more easily, including a new UI, \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/windows-11-beta-duplicate-tabs/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eduplicating tabs\u003c/a\u003e, and using \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/windows-11-file-explorer-gallery-view-insiders/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eGallery view for photos\u003c/a\u003e. Another feature you may want to consider modifying is the home page, which, if you’re not a fan, can be removed by tweaking the Windows Registry.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"what-is-the-home-button-in-file-explorer\"\u003e What is the Home button in File Explorer? \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Home button represents the first landing page you see after launching File Explorer in Windows 11. It provides essential access to frequently used files and folders and displays recently pinned items. You know when you’re in the home location by the presence of the Home button at the top of the left panel. So, when you remove the button, you effectively remove the entire home page.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/windows-11-file-explorer-home-button.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/windows-11-file-explorer-home-button.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/windows-11-file-explorer-home-button.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/windows-11-file-explorer-home-button.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/windows-11-file-explorer-home-button.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/windows-11-file-explorer-home-button.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/windows-11-file-explorer-home-button.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/windows-11-file-explorer-home-button.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/windows-11-file-explorer-home-button.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1049\" height=\"739\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Showing the File Explorer Home Button on Windows 11\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/windows-11-file-explorer-home-button.png\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/windows-11-file-explorer-home-button.png\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhile the average user welcomes the File Explorer home page, you might prefer to remove it if you are more of a technical user. However, removing it isn’t as basic as toggling a switch on or off in settings. Instead, you must hack the Registry, which can be risky if you are not an experienced user and are unsure what you’re doing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"9437-45cb-b07ea293c989\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/registry-tweaks-for-windows-11/\"\u003e\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/registry-editor.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/registry-editor.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/registry-editor.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/registry-editor.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/registry-editor.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/registry-editor.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/registry-editor.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/registry-editor.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/registry-editor.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"3840\" height=\"2160\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"The Windows 11 Registry Editor open on a Uperfect UGame K118 monitor\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/registry-editor.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/registry-editor.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch5\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/registry-tweaks-for-windows-11/\" title=\"11 Registry Editor tweaks every Windows 11 user needs to know\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e 11 Registry Editor tweaks every Windows 11 user needs to know \u003c/a\u003e \u003c/h5\u003e\u003cp\u003eDespite the risks associated with using it, the Registry Editor has many options that you can modify to improve your Windows 11 experience\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"remove-the-home-tab-from-file-explorer\"\u003e Remove the Home Tab from File Explorer \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf you are familiar with tweaking the Registry, removing the home button and having it open to \u0026#34;This PC\u0026#34; is straightforward.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv id=\"custom_block_8\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHacking or tweaking the Windows Registry isn’t for the faint of heart. Modifying a wrong value can cause your system to become unstable or worse. Before proceeding, \n\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/how-back-up-windows-11-pc/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eback up your PC\u003c/a\u003e\n or, at a minimum, \n\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/create-and-utilize-restore-point-windows/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ecreate a system restore point\u003c/a\u003e\n so you can restore your data if something goes awry.\u003c/p\u003e\n \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\u003col\u003e\u003cli\u003e Press \u003cstrong\u003eWindows key + R \u003c/strong\u003eto open the Run dialog, type \u003cstrong\u003eregedit\u003c/strong\u003e, and click \u003cstrong\u003eOK\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/run-dialog-regedit-open-registry.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/run-dialog-regedit-open-registry.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/run-dialog-regedit-open-registry.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/run-dialog-regedit-open-registry.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/run-dialog-regedit-open-registry.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/run-dialog-regedit-open-registry.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/run-dialog-regedit-open-registry.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/run-dialog-regedit-open-registry.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/run-dialog-regedit-open-registry.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1006\" height=\"436\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Showing how to launch Registry from the Run dialog box\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/run-dialog-regedit-open-registry.png\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/run-dialog-regedit-open-registry.png\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Navigate to \u003cem\u003eHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Explorer\u003c/em\u003e \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Right-click the Explorer key and select \u003cstrong\u003eNew \u0026gt; DWORD (32-bit) Value\u003c/strong\u003e from the context menu.\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/edit-explorer-key-to-create-new-dword-32-bit-value.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/edit-explorer-key-to-create-new-dword-32-bit-value.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/edit-explorer-key-to-create-new-dword-32-bit-value.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/edit-explorer-key-to-create-new-dword-32-bit-value.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/edit-explorer-key-to-create-new-dword-32-bit-value.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/edit-explorer-key-to-create-new-dword-32-bit-value.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/edit-explorer-key-to-create-new-dword-32-bit-value.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/edit-explorer-key-to-create-new-dword-32-bit-value.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/edit-explorer-key-to-create-new-dword-32-bit-value.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1156\" height=\"664\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Create a new DWORD 32-bit value in Windows Registry\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/edit-explorer-key-to-create-new-dword-32-bit-value.png\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/edit-explorer-key-to-create-new-dword-32-bit-value.png\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Type \u003cstrong\u003eHubMode\u003c/strong\u003e for the new value\u0026#39;s name and press \u003cstrong\u003eEnter\u003c/strong\u003e to confirm. \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Right-click the new \u003cstrong\u003eHubMode\u003c/strong\u003e key and select \u003cstrong\u003eModify\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/3-modify-hubmode-menu.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/3-modify-hubmode-menu.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/3-modify-hubmode-menu.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/3-modify-hubmode-menu.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/3-modify-hubmode-menu.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/3-modify-hubmode-menu.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/3-modify-hubmode-menu.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/3-modify-hubmode-menu.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/3-modify-hubmode-menu.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"929\" height=\"348\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Selecting modify from right-click HubMode Menu\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/3-modify-hubmode-menu.png\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/3-modify-hubmode-menu.png\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Change the \u003cstrong\u003eValue data\u003c/strong\u003e field for the HubMode key from 0 to \u003cstrong\u003e1\u003c/strong\u003e and click \u003cstrong\u003eOK\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/6-change-value-from-0-to-1.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/6-change-value-from-0-to-1.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/6-change-value-from-0-to-1.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/6-change-value-from-0-to-1.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/6-change-value-from-0-to-1.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/6-change-value-from-0-to-1.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/6-change-value-from-0-to-1.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/6-change-value-from-0-to-1.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/6-change-value-from-0-to-1.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"978\" height=\"508\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Changing HubMode Value data to 1 and click OK\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/6-change-value-from-0-to-1.png\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/6-change-value-from-0-to-1.png\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Head to \u003cem\u003eHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Explorer\\Desktop\\NameSpace\u003c/em\u003e \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Locate and right-click the \u003cstrong\u003e{f874310e-b6b7-47dc-bc84-b9e6b38f5903}\u003c/strong\u003e key and click \u003cstrong\u003eDelete\u003c/strong\u003e from the menu that appears.\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/7-showing-deleting-key-in-file-explorer-in-windows-registry.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/7-showing-deleting-key-in-file-explorer-in-windows-registry.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/7-showing-deleting-key-in-file-explorer-in-windows-registry.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/7-showing-deleting-key-in-file-explorer-in-windows-registry.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/7-showing-deleting-key-in-file-explorer-in-windows-registry.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/7-showing-deleting-key-in-file-explorer-in-windows-registry.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/7-showing-deleting-key-in-file-explorer-in-windows-registry.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/7-showing-deleting-key-in-file-explorer-in-windows-registry.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/7-showing-deleting-key-in-file-explorer-in-windows-registry.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1047\" height=\"419\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Showing the Delete key after right clicking key in the Windows Registry\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/7-showing-deleting-key-in-file-explorer-in-windows-registry.png\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/7-showing-deleting-key-in-file-explorer-in-windows-registry.png\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Restart File Explorer to confirm and complete the process. \u003c/li\u003e \n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"file-explorer-free-of-a-home-button\"\u003e File Explorer free of a home button \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOnce you finish the steps, when you open \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/file-explorer-windows-11/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eFile Explorer\u003c/a\u003e, the home button and page will no longer appear and default to the \u0026#34;\u003cstrong\u003eThis PC\u003c/strong\u003e\u0026#34; view. If you still see it, go through the steps again to verify that they are being executed properly. It’s also worth mentioning that you might need to restart your PC to confirm that the Registry changes have been properly synced.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/8-home-button-and-page-removed-from-file-explorer-defaults-to-this-pc.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/8-home-button-and-page-removed-from-file-explorer-defaults-to-this-pc.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/8-home-button-and-page-removed-from-file-explorer-defaults-to-this-pc.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/8-home-button-and-page-removed-from-file-explorer-defaults-to-this-pc.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/8-home-button-and-page-removed-from-file-explorer-defaults-to-this-pc.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/8-home-button-and-page-removed-from-file-explorer-defaults-to-this-pc.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/8-home-button-and-page-removed-from-file-explorer-defaults-to-this-pc.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/8-home-button-and-page-removed-from-file-explorer-defaults-to-this-pc.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/8-home-button-and-page-removed-from-file-explorer-defaults-to-this-pc.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"800\" height=\"564\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Showing Windows 11 File Explorer opening to This PC after Registry hack\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/8-home-button-and-page-removed-from-file-explorer-defaults-to-this-pc.png\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/8-home-button-and-page-removed-from-file-explorer-defaults-to-this-pc.png\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e It’s also important to mention that you’ll still find the Home entry in the \u003cstrong\u003eFolder Options\u003c/strong\u003e setting. However, it will be unavailable until you restore the Registry settings you removed, as outlined in the above steps.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n    \n        \n\n    \n\n        \n\n\n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                    \n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
